analysis: The documents primarily focus on the establishment, modification, and administration of wildlife refuges and bird sanctuaries. They involve the withdrawal of public lands from settlement for conservation purposes, often specifying the types of wildlife to be protected (migratory birds) and outlining regulations against hunting or disturbing the wildlife. Several orders also deal with land acquisition and transfer of jurisdiction between government departments (Agriculture, Interior, Treasury) to manage these refuges. A common theme is the collaboration between federal and state entities in managing these areas. One order establishes a committee to advise on a wilderness sanctuary program.
title: Wildlife Refuge and Bird Sanctuary Land Management
